main event: A witness in Palacios, Texas reported observing two unidentified objects in the sky on February 16, 1959.
interesting points: The objects were observed through ground-based radar and were described as having a 'tremendous' speed, but the witness could not estimate the exact speed.
The witness could not estimate the distance of the objects, but noted they were not large enough to be observed visually at close range.
The witness reported seeing the objects move in an erratic manner, with the main object changing size and shape before disappearing.
The witness sketched diagrams showing the positions and movements of the objects.
The witness compared the objects to a description from a poem they had written in 1946, speculating about new methods of flying that could overcome gravity.
